body:
### Highlights

**Task documentation improvements** - The `mise generate task-docs` command now supports a `--index` flag and uses task names when generating multi-file documentation with `--multi`. This gives you better control over how your task documentation is organized and named. [#7944](https://github.com/jdx/mise/pull/7944)

**Tool stub generation with --lock** - You can now generate tool stubs with locked versions using `mise generate tool-stub --lock`, making it easier to pin exact tool versions in your generated stubs. [#7948](https://github.com/jdx/mise/pull/7948)

**Plugin shadowing warnings** - mise now warns you when an env plugin shadows a tool from the registry, helping you avoid confusion when a local plugin name conflicts with a well-known tool. [#7953](https://github.com/jdx/mise/pull/7953)

**Lua log module for vfox plugins** - Plugin authors can now use a dedicated logging module to output debug information, warnings, and errors from their Lua plugins. [#7949](https://github.com/jdx/mise/pull/7949)

### Bug Fixes

- Fixed handling of `file://` URLs in the registry's `normalize_remote` function [#7947](https://github.com/jdx/mise/pull/7947)
- Fixed LuaLS warnings in vfox test fixtures and added linting [#7946](https://github.com/jdx/mise/pull/7946)

### Internal Changes

- Unified the `deprecated_at!` macro to provide consistent deprecation warnings [#7957](https://github.com/jdx/mise/pull/7957)

---

Full documentation: https://mise.jdx.dev/
